		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The prediction ability and parsimony of multivariate models of data set representing infrared spectra with peak shifts are significantly reduced.By performing multivariate modelling on the underlying non-linear peak parameters the effect of peak shifts are reduced to variations in scalar values of the peak position parameters.  Multivariate modelling on such parameters does not suffer from the same problems as are encountered when using the raw spectra profiles.In order to do this efficiently, a faster method for estimating non-linear peak parameters for a large number of spectroscopic profiles must be constructed.  The strategy suggested is to use artificial neural networks that have been trained on data with know parameter values to create a non-linear map between the space of spectral profiles and the peak parameters.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
